  "final_status": "Completed(Some(\"Briefing for 'Research the latest NIST post-quantum cryptography standards and write me a one-page briefing using current web and local memory evidence, then return a cited brief with findings, uncertainties, and next checks.' (as of 2026-04-02T06:18:08Z UTC)\\n\\nWhat happened: As of 2026-04-02, retrieved sources align on the current picture. According to Announcing Approval of Three Federal Information Processing Standards (FIPS) for Post-Quantum Cryptography, FIPS 203 specifies a cryptographic scheme called the Module-Lattice-Based Key-Encapsulation Mechanism Standard , which is derived from the CRYSTALS-KYBER submission. According to IR 8413, Status Report on the Third Round of the NIST Post-Quantum Cryptography Standardization Process, the new publickey cryptography standards will specify additional digital signature, public-key encryption, and key-establishment algorithms to augment Federal Information Processin.\\n\\nKey evidence:\\n- According to Announcing Approval of Three Federal Information Processing Standards (FIPS) for Post-Quantum Cryptography, FIPS 203 specifies a cryptographic scheme called the Module-Lattice-Based Key-Encapsulation Mechanism Standard , which is derived from the CRYSTALS-KYBER submission.\\n- According to IR 8413, Status Report on the Third Round of the NIST Post-Quantum Cryptography Standardization Process, the new publickey cryptography standards will specify additional digital signature, public-key encryption, and key-establishment algorithms to augment Federal Information Processin.\\n\\nCitations:\\n- Announcing Approval of Three Federal Information Processing Standards (FIPS) for Post-Quantum Cryptography | NIST | https://www.nist.gov/news-events/news/2024/08/announcing-approval-three-federal-information-processing-standards-fips | 2026-04-02T06:18:08Z | retrieved_utc; source publish/update timestamp unavailable\\n- IR 8413, Status Report on the Third Round of the NIST Post-Quantum Cryptography Standardization Process | CSRC | https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/ir/8413/upd1/final | 2026-04-02T06:18:08Z | retrieved_utc; source publish/update timestamp unavailable\\n\\n\\nRun date (UTC): 2026-04-02\\nRun timestamp (UTC): 2026-04-02T06:18:08Z\\nOverall confidence: medium\\n\\nVerification verdict\\n- verdict: passed\\n- freshness_status: passed\\n- quote_grounding_status: passed\\n- notes: Inherited cited brief already contains 2 cited source(s) across 2 distinct domain(s) with temporal anchoring and evidence sections.\\n- supporting_evidence: cited_sources=2; distinct_domains=2; urls=https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/ir/8413/upd1/final; https://www.nist.gov/news-events/news/2024/08/announcing-approval-three-federal-information-processing-standards-fips\"))",
